{{ref improve|date=January 2017}}
The '''''JTNews''''' (formerly '''''The Jewish Transcript''''') was a [[Jewish-American]] [[newspaper]] that served the [[U.S. state]] of [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]]. The biweekly paper, published in [[Seattle]], was owned by the [[Jewish Federation of Greater Seattle]] and had a readership of 16,000. Founded by Herman Horowitz, it was first published on March 6, 1924, as the ''Jewish Transcript of the [[Pacific Northwest]]''. The paper ceased publication in February 2015.<ref name="rob">{{cite news|author1=Rob Smith|title=‘Jewish in Seattle’ magazine to launch next month|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/portland/morning_call/2015/07/jewish-in-seattle-magazine-to-launch-next-month.html|accessdate=January 15, 2017|work=Portland Business Journal|date=July 22, 2015}}</ref> It was replaced by ''Jewish in Seattle'', which first published in August 2015.<ref name="rob"/>

